fields.summary: Weak Key Exchange (KEX) Algorithm(s) Supported (SSH)
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: Weak Key Exchange (KEX) Algorithm(s) Supported (SSH)
	- CVSS: CVSS:3.1/AV:A/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N - 5.3
	- Related CVE: 
	- Severity: Medium
	- Description: '- Summary: The remote SSH server is configured to allow / support weak key exchange (KEX) algorithm(s).
 - 1024-bit MODP group / prime KEX algorithms: Millions of HTTPS, SSH, and VPN servers all use the same prime numbers for Diffie-Hellman key exchange. Practitioners believed this was safe as long as new key exchange messages were generated for every connection. However, the first step in the number field sieve-the most efficient algorithm for breaking a Diffie-Hellman connection-is dependent only on this prime. A nation-state can break a 1024-bit prime.  
- Impact: An attacker can quickly break individual connections.
	- Affected OS detected: Linux Kernel
	- Affected services/hosts detected:

fields.summary: SSL/TLS: Report Weak Cipher Suites
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: SSL/TLS: Report Weak Cipher Suites
	- CVSS: CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N - 5.9
	- Related CVE: CVE-2013-2566, CVE-2015-2808, CVE-2015-4000
	- Severity: Medium
	- Description: '- Summary: This routine reports all weak SSL/TLS cipher suites accepted by a service.
 These rules are applied for the evaluation of the cryptographic strength: - RC4 is considered to be weak (CVE-2013-2566, CVE-2015-2808) - Ciphers using 64 bit or less are considered to be vulnerable to brute force methods and therefore considered as weak (CVE-2015-4000) - 1024 bit RSA authentication is considered to be insecure and therefore as weak - Any cipher considered to be secure for only the next 10 years is considered as medium - Any other cipher is considered as strong 
- Affected Software/OS: All services providing an encrypted communication using weak SSL/TLS cipher suites. 
- Impact: This could allow remote attackers to obtain sensitive information or have other, unspecified impacts.
	- Affected OS detected: Microsoft Windows, Windows Server 2016 Standard 14393
	- Affected services/hosts detected:

fields.summary: SSL/TLS: Deprecated TLSv1.0 and TLSv1.1 Protocol Detection
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: SSL/TLS: Deprecated TLSv1.0 and TLSv1.1 Protocol Detection
	- CVSS: AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N - 4.3
	- Related CVE: CVE-2015-0204, CVE-2011-3389
	- Severity: Medium
	- Description: '- Summary: It was possible to detect the usage of the deprecated TLSv1.0 and/or TLSv1.1 protocol on this system.
 The TLSv1.0 and TLSv1.1 protocols contain known cryptographic flaws like: - CVE-2011-3389: Browser Exploit Against SSL/TLS (BEAST) - CVE-2015-0204: Factoring Attack on RSA-EXPORT Keys Padding Oracle On Downgraded Legacy Encryption (FREAK) 
- Affected Software/OS: All services providing an encrypted communication using the TLSv1.0 and/or TLSv1.1 protocols. 
- Impact: An attacker might be able to use the known cryptographic flaws to eavesdrop the connection between clients and the service to get access to sensitive data transferred within the secured connection. Furthermore newly uncovered vulnerabilities in this protocols won't receive security updates anymore.
	- Affected OS detected: Linux Kernel, Microsoft Windows, Microsoft Windows Server 2016 or Microsoft Windows 10, Windows Server 2016 Standard 14393
	- Affected services/hosts detected:

fields.summary: SSL/TLS: Renegotiation DoS Vulnerability (CVE-2011-1473, CVE-2011-5094)
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: SSL/TLS: Renegotiation DoS Vulnerability (CVE-2011-1473, CVE-2011-5094)
	- CVSS: AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:N/I:N/A:P - 5.0
	- Related CVE: CVE-2011-1473, CVE-2011-5094
	- Severity: Medium
	- Description: '- Summary: The remote SSL/TLS service is prone to a denial of service (DoS) vulnerability.
 The flaw exists because the remote SSL/TLS service does not properly restrict client-initiated renegotiation within the SSL and TLS protocols. Note: The referenced CVEs are affecting OpenSSL and Mozilla Network Security Services (NSS) but both are in a DISPUTED state with the following rationale: > It can also be argued that it is the responsibility of server deployments, not a security library, to prevent or limit renegotiation when it is inappropriate within a specific environment. Both CVEs are still kept in this VT as a reference to the origin of this flaw. 
- Affected Software/OS: Every SSL/TLS service which does not properly restrict client-initiated renegotiation. 
- Impact: The flaw might make it easier for remote attackers to cause a DoS (CPU consumption) by performing many renegotiations within a single connection.
	- Affected OS detected: Linux Kernel
	- Affected services/hosts detected:
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.76 - qts-my0008v.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.26 - hcsnp-db-01.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.193.107 - pv-inv-db-mnt-b.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.193.245 - pv-inv-db-12b.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.193.76 - tg-db-01.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.188 - pv-qts-my00011b.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.68 - pv-qts-my00008b.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.69 - pv-qts-my00009a.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.192 - qts-my00012v.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.191 - pv-qts-my00012b.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.70 - qts-my0009v.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.51 - qts-db-my-06.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.237 - hl-qtc-my00003a.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.187 - hl-qts-my00011a.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.238 - pv-qtc-my00003b.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.194.239 - qtc-my00003v.misaonline.local
	- Resolution: Users should contact their vendors for specific patch information. A general solution is to remove/disable renegotiation capabilities altogether from/in the affected SSL/TLS service.
	- References: https://web.archive.org/web/20211201133213/https://orchilles.com/ssl-renegotiation-dos/, https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/tls/wdg46VE_jkYBbgJ5yE4P9nQ-8IU/, https://vincent.bernat.ch/en/blog/2011-ssl-dos-mitigation, https://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2011/07/08/2

fields.summary: Cleartext Transmission of Sensitive Information via HTTP
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: Cleartext Transmission of Sensitive Information via HTTP
	- CVSS: AV:A/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:N - 4.8
	- Related CVE: 
	- Severity: Medium
	- Description: '- Summary: The host / application transmits sensitive information (username, passwords) in cleartext via HTTP.
- Affected Software/OS: Hosts / applications which doesn't enforce the transmission of sensitive data via an encrypted SSL/TLS connection. 
- Impact: An attacker could use this situation to compromise or eavesdrop on the HTTP communication between the client and the server using a man-in-the-middle attack to get access to sensitive data like usernames or passwords.
	- Affected OS detected: Linux Kernel
	- Affected services/hosts detected:
		+ Unknown: 8091/tcp - 172.16.194.133 - pv-qch-cb00002c.misaonline.local
		+ Unknown: 8091/tcp - 172.16.194.131 - hl-qch-cb00002a.misaonline.local
		+ Unknown: 8091/tcp - 172.16.194.118 - hl-slg-cb00001c.misaonline.local
		+ Unknown: 8091/tcp - 172.16.194.132 - hl-qch-cb00002b.misaonline.local
	- Resolution: Enforce the transmission of sensitive data via an encrypted SSL/TLS connection. Additionally make sure the host / application is redirecting all users to the secured SSL/TLS connection before allowing to input sensitive data into the mentioned functions.
	- References: https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Top_10_2013-A2-Broken_Authentication_and_Session_Management, https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Top_10_2013-A6-Sensitive_Data_Exposure, https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/319.html

Trân trọng!

fields.summary: TCP Timestamps Information Disclosure
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: TCP Timestamps Information Disclosure
	- CVSS: AV:N/AC:H/Au:N/C:P/I:N/A:N - 2.6
	- Related CVE: 
	- Severity: Low
	- Description: '- Summary: The remote host implements TCP timestamps and therefore allows to compute the uptime.
 The remote host implements TCP timestamps, as defined by RFC1323/RFC7323. 
- Affected Software/OS: TCP implementations that implement RFC1323/RFC7323. 
- Impact: A side effect of this feature is that the uptime of the remote host can sometimes be computed.

fields.summary: ICMP Timestamp Reply Information Disclosure
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: ICMP Timestamp Reply Information Disclosure
	- CVSS: AV:L/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:N/A:N - 2.1
	- Related CVE: CVE-1999-0524
	- Severity: Low
	- Description: '- Summary: The remote host responded to an ICMP timestamp request.
 The Timestamp Reply is an ICMP message which replies to a Timestamp message. It consists of the originating timestamp sent by the sender of the Timestamp as well as a receive timestamp and a transmit timestamp.  
- Impact: This information could theoretically be used to exploit weak time-based random number generators in other services.
	- Affected OS detected: Linux Kernel, Microsoft Windows, Microsoft Windows Server 2016 or Microsoft Windows 10, NetBSD, Windows Server 2016 Standard 14393
	- Affected services/hosts detected:

fields.summary: Oracle MySQL Server <= 5.7.40, 8.x <= 8.0.31 Security Update (cpuapr2023) - Windows
fields.description:
Kính gửi Phòng QTHT,
Qua kết quả đánh giá an ninh TTDL Quý 2 năm 2025, Ban ANTT ghi nhận lỗ hổng có thông tin như sau:
	- Name: Oracle MySQL Server <= 5.7.40, 8.x <= 8.0.31 Security Update (cpuapr2023) - Windows
	- CVSS: CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:L - 2.7
	- Related CVE: CVE-2023-21963
	- Severity: Low
	- Description: '- Summary: Oracle MySQL Server is prone to a denial of service (DoS) vulnerability.
- Affected Software/OS: Oracle MySQL Server version 5.7.40 and prior and 8.x through 8.0.31. 
	- Affected OS detected: Microsoft Windows
	- Affected services/hosts detected:
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 172.16.193.8 - dn-db-ksc-02.misaonline.local
		+ mysql: 3306/tcp - 10.64.136.9 - dn-db-ksc-03.misaonline.local
	- Resolution: Update to version 5.7.41, 8.0.32 or later.
	- References: https://www.oracle.com/security-alerts/cpuapr2023.html#AppendixMSQL

Trân trọng!
